			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>Manually authenticate a user with the given set of data. Rather than checking a user's
credentials, this method allows you to manually specify a user for whom you'd like to
initialize an authenticated session.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<p>By default, before writing the data to the session, the <code>set()</code> method of the named
configuration's adapter receives the data to be written, and has an opportunity to modify
or reject it.</p>
					</div>
							</section>

